            <div1 type="letter">
                
                <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.21-23_0001a" />
            <note type="curatorial"><unclear>1</unclear>35 - 2</note>
            
            <fw type="letterhead">
                    Skyrim Farm              <hi rend="caps">JOHN G. NEIHARDT</hi>          <note type="curatorial">Aly Collection</note>
                <lb/>
                    Route 7
                <lb/>
                    Columbia, Mo.
            </fw>
                
                <opener>
                    <dateline>June 8, '61</dateline>
                    
                    
                    <salute>Dear Lucile:</salute>
                </opener>
                    <p>Here is good news! The Nebraska Legislature has today voted unanimously to place a bronze bust of me in the Hall of Fame, State Capitol Building, Lincoln. This is quite a triumph, as the Bill establishing the Hall of Fame (passed a few weeks ago) stipulates that <hi rend="underline">no living person</hi> shall be eligible to the honor. There was a 
                        state-wide movement urging
                        
                        <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.21-23_0001b"/>
                        <fw type="authorial">-2-</fw>
                        
                        <del><unclear>an exception</unclear></del>
                        that an exception be made in my case &#8212; the newspapers, the University, the colleges, the Governor etc all endorsing the movement.</p>
                
                    <p>Here's another nice thing that should be of use to you in the biography. A certain Lee Vernon of Chicago, now 73 years old and retired from 40 years of teaching in Chicago schools, writes me that he (or is it she?) remembers me as a young man <del><unclear>walking</unclear></del>
                        
                        <fw type="curatorial">21</fw>
                        <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.21-23_0002a"/>
                        <fw type="authorial">-3-</fw>
                        
                        walking past the country <del/> school in Wayne County where he, a kid, was attending. He saw me once after that, but has <del><unclear>heard</unclear></del> heard of me often, &amp; now he feels the urge to write!</p>
                
                <p>How could a kid of 8-10 years be so impressed? Evidently I just walked by the school while the kids were playing, and stopped to say something pleasant to the youngsters.
                        
                        <pb facs="nei.j4c.32.21-23_0002b"/>
                        <fw type="authorial">-4-</fw>
                        
                        I wonder where I was going. I walked so much &amp; so far <del/><add>those</add> days. To think the boy (or is Lee a girl?) did not forget!!</p>
                
                    <p>Well, I'll be seeing you'ns before too long. I dread it terribly, because I don't like you people at all. Also I don't like Perky either.</p>
                
                <p>Otherwise, the same old affection.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>John N.</signed>
                </closer>
                   
                <postscript><p>New edition of the <hi rend="underline">Cycle</hi> on or before Sep 1st Maroon binding this time</p></postscript>
                    
                    <fw type="curatorial">22</fw>
            </div1>
            
            
            
